thread.title_full: St. Norbert Knights cruise to victory

title: St. Norbert Knights cruise to victory
text:
St. Norbert Knights cruise to victory Oct. 24, 2015 10:39 p.m. 
St. Norbert scored on four of its first five possessions and shut out host Beloit, 33-0, Saturday to improve to 7-0 overall, its best start since the 2007 season. 
The Green Knights (3-0 Midwest Conference North) started 10-0 in '07. 
St. Norbert outgained Beloit, 473-196, in total offense. The defense held Beloit standout running back Mason Dixon to 45 yards on 17 carries. Dixon entered the game averaging 148 yards per game. 
Elijah Fort scored three touchdowns for St. Norbert, on a 5-yard pass and two 1-yard runs. 
Lakeland 47, Aurora 40 (2 OT): Quarterback Michael Whitley scored on an 8-yard run in the second overtime period to boost the Muskies (5-2, 3-0 Northern Athletics Conference) over the host Spartans (3-4, 2-2). 
In a contest that was tight throughout, Aurora tied it at 40 with 37 seconds left in regulation on a 16-yard pass from Geron Rogers to Danny Loguirato. 
Whitley finished with 126 yards and four touchdowns on the ground. He passed for 363 yards and three TDs. 
Carroll 15, Ripon 6: Kyle Burlingame passed for 218 yards and two touchdowns to help lead the Pioneers (4-3, 2-1 MWC North) to a narrow victory over the Red Hawks (4-3, 1-2) in Waukesha. 
Bennett Kothe rushed for 123 yards and caught two passes for 77 yards and a touchdown. 
Carthage 39, Augustana (Ill.) 27: Ethan Olles, making his first collegiate start, went 16 for 26 for 197 yards and three touchdowns as the Red Men (3-4, 2-2 CCIW) outlasted the Vikings (2-5, 1-3) in Rock Island, Ill. 
Tristan Peterson added two rushing touchdowns for Carthage. 
Macalester 35, Lawrence 7: Quarterback Alec Beatty ran 13 times for 179 yards and two touchdowns as the Scots (4-3, 2-1 MWC North) barreled past the Vikings (1-6, 0-3) in Appleton. 
Macalester finished with 416 rushing yards as Zandy Stowell added 193 yards and two TDs on the ground. The Scots outgained Lawrence in total yardage, 446-160. 
Concordia (Wis.) 15, Rockford 7: Aaron Nixon's two touchdown passes, to Aaron Brown and Derrick Etsfan, were enough to boost the Falcons (3-4, 3-1 NACC) over the host Regents (2-5, 0-3).
